# CLAUDE.md Version Guard

## Trigger

When ANY of these files change, verify CLAUDE.md Tech Stack section is still accurate:

| File changed | Check in CLAUDE.md |
|---|---|
| `package.json` | Vite version, React version, new major deps |
| `vite.config.*` | `base` path, build config, plugins |
| `src/App.tsx` | Router type (BrowserRouter vs HashRouter), route list |
| `src/main.tsx` | Provider tree, CSS imports |
| `src/styles/app.css` | Font imports (`@import url(...)` → font names) |
| `index.html` | CDN links, meta tags, base href |
| `tsconfig*.json` | Target, module resolution |

## What to update

In `CLAUDE.md` under `## Tech Stack`:
- Framework + version (React X + TypeScript X + Vite X)
- CSS approach (Bootstrap version, animation lib)
- Fonts (check actual `@import` in app.css, not assumptions)
- Router type (check actual component in App.tsx)
- Deploy target (check vite.config `base` + deploy workflow)

## Why this exists

CLAUDE.md is loaded at every AI session start. Stale info = wrong assumptions = wrong code.
Historical drift found during audit: Vite 6→7, Inter→DM Sans, HashRouter→BrowserRouter — all wrong in CLAUDE.md while code had moved on.
